Patricia barreled toward southwestern Mexico Friday as a monster Category 5 storm, the strongest ever in the Western Hemisphere. Locals and tourists were either hunkering down or trying to make last-minute escapes ahead of what forecasters called a "potentially catastrophic landfall" later in the day.

Patricia barreled toward southwestern ... more Image 31 of 31 Weekend forecast forces event planners to switch gears 1 / 31 Back to Gallery Storms hitting Texas from all sides are wreaking havoc with Houston-area event planners.
While major events such as Texas Renaissance Festival and the Texian Market Days at George Ranch will go on rain or shine, there have been many others that are being rescheduled, modified or canceled.
The Houston Zombie Walk ’s Halloween Fest at Hughes Hangar, 2811 Washington, is being shortened and will not include the traditional zombie walk down Washington Avenue. The kids’ carnival and zombie laser tag have also been canceled. New fest hours are 4-10 p.m. Tickets are $10. Information: houstonishalloween.com .
CANCELLATIONS
The Tomball Bluegrass Festival, which was to have taken place Saturday, has been moved to Nov. 15. Information: tomballtx.gov .
Little Woodrow’s-Midtown, 2306 Brazos, has canceled Saturday’s Wild Game Cookoff .
The Oaks Business Association (TOBA) has canceled Saturday’s Fall Festival, which was to be held at Candlelight Park.
Midtown’s monthly Art in the Park , which was scheduled for Saturday, has been canceled.
RESCHEDULED EVENTS
League City's annual Harvest Festival , which was to be Saturday, has been rescheduled. It will now be 6-10 p.m. Oct. 30 at 175 Bay Area Blvd. Information: leaguecity.com .
The Orange Show has rescheduled its Fall Funday in Smither Park. The event will now be 11 a.m.-2 p.m. Oct. 31 at 2441 Munger. Information: orangshow.org .
The annual Halloween Car Show at the National Museum of Funeral History , 415 Barren Springs, has been rescheduled for 10 a.m.-3 p.m. Oct. 31. Information: nmfh.org .
Bike Houston’s Moonlight Ramble , which was to have rolled out at midnight Saturday, has been rescheduled for Nov. 7. Information: bikehouston.org .
Our Lady of Guadalupe ‘s Parish Fall Festival has been moved to 9 a.m.-9 p.m. Nov. 8 at 2405 Navigation. Information: olghouston.org .
Meyerland’s Afternoon in the Park has been moved to 2-5 p.m. Nov. 15 at Godwin Park, 5101 Rutherglenn. Information: meyerland.net .
Tacolandia , an event scheduled for Saturday at Buffalo Bayou Park, has been rescheduled. The event now will be 4-7 p.m. Nov. 14 at 105 Sabine. Information: ticketfly.com .
